Approach 2: Modified Binary Search (Your Approach)
Intuition

This approach is almost the same as LeetCode 33.

The only difference is handling duplicates.

If

nums[mid] == nums[left]

then we cannot determine which half is sorted.

So simply move

left++;

and continue searching.

Otherwise,

If the left half is sorted → check whether the target lies there.
Else → the right half is sorted.
Java (Your Code)
class Solution {
    public boolean search(int[] nums, int target) {

        int left = 0;
        int right = nums.length - 1;

        while (left <= right) {

            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;

            if (nums[mid] == target) {
                return true;
            }

            // Duplicate case
            if (nums[mid] == nums[left]) {
                left++;
                continue;
            }

            // Left half is sorted
            if (nums[left] <= nums[mid]) {

                if (nums[left] <= target &&
                    target < nums[mid]) {

                    right = mid - 1;

                } else {

                    left = mid + 1;
                }
            }

            // Right half is sorted
            else {

                if (nums[mid] < target &&
                    target <= nums[right]) {

                    left = mid + 1;

                } else {

                    right = mid - 1;
                }
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
}
